So you have done the right this. All you need is to get all values from `JSONArray`, convert them separately and build an array of `String`.

```java
public static String toString(JSONArray jsonArray) {
    return IntStream.rangeClosed(0, jsonArray.length())
            .mapToObj(i -&gt; String.format(&quot;%.2f&quot;, (BigDecimal) jsonArray.get(i)))
            .collect(Collectors.joining(&quot;,&quot;, &quot;[&quot;, &quot;]&quot;));
}
```

